48
00:02:54,599 --> 00:02:55,560
So do I.

49
00:02:58,000 --> 00:03:00,400
The System likes everything
the villainess believes in.

50
00:03:01,199 --> 00:03:02,560
Due to her existence,

51
00:03:03,400 --> 00:03:05,080
this world is now more interesting.

52
00:03:05,759 --> 00:03:07,000
In fact, the villainess

53
00:03:07,199 --> 00:03:10,360
is considered an unexpected glitch

54
00:03:10,360 --> 00:03:11,280
in this whole setup?

55
00:03:11,560 --> 00:03:12,400
An unexpected glitch?

56
00:03:15,280 --> 00:03:16,800
Not even my parents dare call me that.

57
00:03:17,960 --> 00:03:20,240
But she's also the only color
in this world

58
00:03:20,400 --> 00:03:22,759
the System can ever touch.

59
00:03:24,199 --> 00:03:25,900
And the System can
no longer stay calm and objective

60
00:03:26,360 --> 00:03:29,759
because of her.

61
00:03:33,199 --> 00:03:34,080
So,

62
00:03:35,360 --> 00:03:37,400
from the very beginning,

63
00:03:37,400 --> 00:03:40,360
the System already had designs
on the villainess.

64
00:03:40,639 --> 00:03:41,439
Yes.

65
00:03:41,960 --> 00:03:43,919
From the very beginning,

66
00:03:43,919 --> 00:03:46,639
the System had gone soft
on the villainess.

67
00:03:47,400 --> 00:03:49,199
No matter how the ending turns out.

68
00:03:53,680 --> 00:03:55,159
Even if there's no ending,

69
00:03:56,400 --> 00:03:57,680
